You said:
my logo colour is not changed
ChatGPT said:
Perfect. This is a very common CSS behavior, and it is easy to fix.
Nothing is broken.

Your logo color is not changing because another CSS rule is overriding it.

We will fix this in the safest beginner way.

WHY THE LOGO COLOR DID NOT CHANGE
Your logo text is:

<h1 class="logo">Hauls by Tom</h1>
But the text color is inherited from this rule:

body {
    color: #eaeaea;
}
Sometimes the browser keeps using this unless we explicitly override it.

FIX IT (100 percent guaranteed)
STEP 1: Open style.css
Right click ‚Üí Open with ‚Üí Notepad

STEP 2: GO TO THE VERY BOTTOM OF THE FILE
Scroll all the way down.

STEP 3: ADD THIS CODE AT THE BOTTOM
Do NOT replace anything.
Just add this as new lines:

.logo {
    color: #c0a060 !important;
}
The !important forces the color.
This is acceptable for beginners and small projects.

STEP 4: SAVE AND REFRESH
Press Ctrl + S

Go to browser

Press Ctrl + F5

Your logo will turn gold.

IF IT STILL DOES NOT CHANGE (VERY RARE)
Then your logo is being styled by a more specific rule.

In that case, add this instead at the bottom:

header .logo {
    color: #c0a060 !important;
}
Save ‚Üí Refresh.

QUICK CONFIRMATION
Reply with one word only:

gold ‚Üí logo turned gold

white ‚Üí still white

I will respond instantly based on your answer.

